\v 3 Say \w to|strong="H3389"\w* them, ‘\w This|strong="H3541"\w* \w is|strong="H3389"\w* \w what|strong="H3541"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3069"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3069"\w* \w says|strong="H3541"\w* \w to|strong="H3389"\w* you people \w of|strong="H3069"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="H3389"\w*: \add It is as though you are a woman who\add* [MET] \w was|strong="H3389"\w* \w born|strong="H4138"\w* \w in|strong="H3389"\w* \w the|strong="H3069"\w* country where \w the|strong="H3069"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3669"\w* people-group lived. \add It is as though\add* [MET] \w your|strong="H3541"\w* father belonged \w to|strong="H3389"\w* \w the|strong="H3069"\w* Amor people-group \w and|strong="H3389"\w* \w your|strong="H3541"\w* mother belonged \w to|strong="H3389"\w* \w the|strong="H3069"\w* Heth people-group.  
