\c 23  
\s1 A parable about Jerusalem and Samaria  
\p
\v 1 \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1697"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w me|strong="H1697"\w*,  
\v 2 “\w You|strong="H1961"\w* human, \add listen to this parable about Jerusalem and Samaria\add*. \w Once|strong="H1961"\w* \w there|strong="H1961"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w two|strong="H8147"\w* \w women|strong="H1323"\w*, \w daughters|strong="H1323"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* same mother.  
\v 3 \w They|strong="H8033"\w* lived \w in|strong="H6213"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*. \w And|strong="H4714"\w* \w from|strong="H4714"\w* \w the|strong="H6213"\w* time \w that|strong="H6213"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w were|strong="H4714"\w* young women, \w they|strong="H8033"\w* became \w prostitutes|strong="H2181"\w*. \w In|strong="H6213"\w* \w that|strong="H6213"\w* land, \add men\add* \w fondled|strong="H1717"\w* \w their|strong="H6213"\w* \w breasts|strong="H7699"\w* \w and|strong="H4714"\w* caressed \w their|strong="H6213"\w* bosoms [DOU].  
